HEADWORD: Revolutionize
<hw>Rev`o*lu"tion*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Revolutioniezed</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Revolutionizing</conjf><pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To change
completely, as by a revolution; <as>as, to <ex>revolutionize</ex> a
government</as>.</def> <rj><au>Ames.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The gospel . . . has <qex>revolutionized</qex> his soul.</q>
